  <static seed="88" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems10.pg">
    <statement><p>A trail<rsq/>s total length is <m>{{\frac{32}{63}}}</m> of a mile. It has two legs. The first leg is <m>{{\frac{2}{7}}}</m> of a mile long. How long is the second leg?</p>
<p>The second leg is <fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of a mile in length.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{2}{9}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is a subtraction problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{32}{63}}} - {{\frac{2}{7}}} 
      \amp = \frac{32}{63}-\frac{2 \cdot 9}{7 \cdot 9} \\
      \amp = \frac{32}{63} - \frac{18}{63} \\
      \amp = \frac{32-18}{63} \\
      \amp = \frac{14}{63} \\
      \amp = {{\frac{2}{9}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The second leg is <m>{{\frac{2}{9}}}</m> of a mile in length.</p>
</solution>
